<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">The Ireblind imp can be a pain in the arse. He kinda blocks a straight west or south wall break. Even with a well geared bunch of us he caused us problems the other day when we tried to break Fear to cr some people.
<br />

<br />
We ended up needing to head SE from zone in, to sorta the middle of the south wall. We got a few more mobs on us than if we'd gone straight west or south, but it meant we were well clear of the Ireblind.
<br />

<br />
We AE'd the resulting 25-30 mobs we'd pulled to middle of south wall. I would only remind you that the scarlings will occasionaly side step you if you're the only Enc there AE stunning, this can be a pain so try to kill those 1st.
<br />

<br />
Apart from that Fear is still pretty straight forward, you just need to avoid the whole SW area of Fear and let the Ireblind chill out without any bother.
<br />

<br />
Nop)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
