<span class="postbody">First off..... North of the Fire Ring is a safe spot,  no wanderers back there!
<br />

<br />
What I did is coerce a bard into meeting me at the fear port in (Hey you're an enchanter, you get people to do what you want!).  Here you are just using the bard for their selos.      With selos and Levitate zone in and run north of the fire ring and camp.      With pathing on west wall  you'll camp out before the speedy Scarlings and Spiders catch up to you.      I've done this with the 100k horse as well.    However with just run3 the scarlings and spiders were way too fast!
<br />

<br />
once camped I logged 2nd box, monk on and zoned in running to the same spot and FD until the aggro is cleared.    Once cleared run near the temple, everything will aggro including your Shissar.    FD with her on the north side of the fire ring  and everything will go back to their spawn spots except her,  she waits around for about 20 minutes before moving back at a snare pace.
<br />

<br />
She regens about 300 HP a tick,   this was easily countered by (eventually) getting 3 DoT's on her for about 160 a tick.   (Strangle, gasping embrase and torment).    Let the monk do the rest and all was happy in Norrath. <img src="images/smiles/icon_axe.gif" alt="icon_axe.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
